observations.recommendation:
a. Strictly adhere to the provision of Section 5 of DILG-DBM JMC No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017, to help achieve the desirable socio-economic and environmental outcomes of the province;
b. Mobilize the concerned offices in the early planning and implementation of the priority projects to avoid incurring possible additional cost as a result of delayed implementation;
c. Inform the intended beneficiaries of the programmed projects so that proper coordination will facilitate in the execution of the projects and the benefits thereof at the earliest possible time; and
d. Prepare a catch up plan and fast tract the implementation of the above-mentioned priority development projects.

1.9 We recommended that Management strictly observe the following course of actions:
1.9.1 Conduct complete physical count of Property, Plant and Equipment to be done by the Inventory Committee;
1.9.2 Maintain the required PPE ledger cards and making sure that all properties are completely reported in the inventory report;
1.9.3 Reconcile the inventory report with the accounting records to determine correctness and/or any losses occasioned by theft or other casualty. In the event that deficiencies/discrepancies exist between the inventory report and accounting records, the necessary adjustment/corrections should be made;
1.9.4 Submit complete and accurate RPCPPE to the Audit Team pursuant to Section 124 of the NGAS for the LGUs, Volume 1.
